# Production environment variables for GitHub Actions
# These should be configured as GitHub repository secrets and variables

# GitHub Secrets (sensitive values):
# AWS_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_ID:role/production-ridelines-xyz-github-actions
# PUBLIC_MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_token_here

# GitHub Variables (non-sensitive values):
# DOMAIN_NAME=ridelines.xyz
# GITHUB_ORG=kreed
# GITHUB_REPO=ridelines-website
# S3_BUCKET_NAME=production-ridelines-xyz-website
# CLOUDFRONT_DISTRIBUTION_ID=EXXXXXXXXXXXXX
# PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.ridelines.xyz

# Environment setup instructions:
# 1. Deploy infrastructure first: push changes to terraform/ directory
# 2. Get AWS role ARN from infrastructure output: tofu output github_actions_role_arn
# 3. Get S3 bucket name from output: tofu output s3_bucket_name
# 4. Get CloudFront distribution ID from output: tofu output cloudfront_distribution_id
# 5. Configure these values in GitHub repository settings